â—‹ V = AP x AB
â—‹ Compare it to the surface normal N
â—‹ side(A, P, N, B) = sign of N * (AP x AB)
â–  side(A, P, N, P)
â–  side(B, C, N, P)
â–  side(C, A, N, P)
â— If theyâ€™re all the same sign, then weâ€™re
inside the triangle, and otherwise, weâ€™re
outside the triangle
â— Cross products between a vector to the
point, and a vector along the edge, give us
something perpendicular to the plane as well
â—‹ By testing that three times, we can
figure out whether the point is inside
or outside the triangle
