â— Index of refraction
â—‹ A ratio
â—‹ (speed of light through a vacuum)/(speed of light through whatever material we
have)
â—‹ Speed of light through a vacuum will be the fastest- larger number
â—‹ Index of refraction will always be >= 1
â—‹
Material Index Õ²
Vacuum 1
air 1.0003
waer 1.33
crown glass ~1.5
ice 1.309
quartz 1.544
diamond 2.417
â— Snellâ€™s Law
â—‹
â—‹ Photons travel the same pathway both forward and backward
â—‹
â—‹ This ^ is important for fiber-optic cable (such a high index of refraction that
unless the light is coming a particular way, then there is none coming out)
