Advanced Effects
â— Soft shadow
â—‹ As we get further from the object, the shadow turns more fuzzy
â— Total shadow area
â—‹ Umbra
â— Partial shadow area
â—‹ Penumbra
â— Glossy surface
â—‹ There is a small reflection
â—‹ Costs more than a perfect mirror
â— Depth of field
â—‹ 1/640 â†’ closer are in focus, the far away is horrible, you can;t see it
â—‹ 1/15 â†’ narrow depth of field, the far away is much less blurry
â— Motion blur
â—‹ The stable portions are in focus, the parts that are moving are out of focus
â–  Ex. a building and a moving car (the building is in focus, the car is not)
â— If we have a point source
â—‹ All the photons are coming from one singular place
â—‹ The relevant geometry is that we just get one big circle of total shadow
â–  Shadows are all about visibility
â—‹ Hard shadow
â—‹
â— If we have a disc as a light source
â—‹ This will be whatâ€™s responsible for a soft shadow
â—‹
â— Hard shadow situation
â—‹
â— Distribution ray tracing say that for a lot less work, we can do a much better job
â—‹ With distribution ray tracing, we can have light rays that go to many different
places
â—‹ Using a shadow ray to say how many rays hit the object and how many donâ€™t
â—‹ Uch more expensive
â—‹ Using a probability distribution of rays towards the light source
â—‹
â—‹ This ^ gets us a soft shadow
