Motion Blur (another effect)
â— What does it mean for a ray to have a different time?
â—‹ If time = 0, then ball is here
â—‹ If time = 1, then ball is here
â—‹ Different positions for ball at different times
â—‹ Cast a bunch of rays, average the ray colors at the different times, and determine
the colors of each ray
Increase Light Samples
â— Cast more rays per pixel
â—
â— Add a bit of randomness to the direction of rays that youâ€™re shooting
â—‹ How to add randomness
â–  Jittered sampling
