sample, each of the above drawings is per pixel
Depth of Field Effects (soft effects)
â— Pinhole camera
â—‹
â—‹ Only let a tiny amount of light through
â—‹ Downside
â–  Friend needs to stay still for 5 minutes
â–  Modern-day solution
â—
â— The light through the middle of the (wide) lens, as well as other
parts of the lens ends up at that specific point. The lens focuses al
the light to a specific point
â— The dotted line is the focal plane of the lens
â— Circle of confusion
â—‹ the range of places where out of focus objects will be
shown
â–  How to use distribution ray tracing to get depth of field effects
â—
â— Distribute rays over the lens
â— Different rays going from different parts of the lens
â— Cast a bunch of rays from different points on the lens, make them
all go through point P, average together those colors
â— They should all intersect at point P
